"We have seen the parallel course of events in the two parents,--the Roman law and the German customs, and in the offspring of those two on English soil with regard to servants, animals, and inanimate things.",0,0,0,0,0,0
We have seen a single germ multiplying and branching into products as different from each other as the flower from the root.,0,0,0,0,0,0
It hardly remains to ask what that germ was.,0,0,0,0,0,0
We have seen that it was the desire of retaliation against the offending thing itself.,1,0,0,0,0,0
"Undoubtedly, it might be argued that many of the rules stated were derived from a seizure of the offending thing as security for reparation, at first, perhaps, outside the law.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"That explanation, as well as the one offered here; would show that modern views of responsibility had not yet been attained, as the owner of the thing might very well not have been the person in fault.",0,0,0,0,0,0
But such has not been the view of those most competent to judge.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"A consideration of the earliest instances will show, as might have been expected, that vengeance, not compensation, and vengeance on the offending thing, was the original object.",0,0,0,0,0,0
The ox in Exodus was to be stoned.,0,0,0,0,0,0
