"/2/ But again, What is foresight of consequences?",0,0,0,0,0,0
"It is a picture of a future state of things called up by knowledge of the present state of things, the future being viewed as standing to the present in the relation of effect to cause.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Again, we must seek a reduction to lower terms.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"If the known present state of things is such that the act done will very certainly cause death, and the probability is a matter of common knowledge, one who does the act, [54] knowing the present state of things, is guilty of murder, and the law will not inquire whether he did actually foresee the consequences or not.",1,1,1,1,1,1
"The test of foresight is not what this very criminal foresaw, but what a man of reasonable prudence would have foreseen.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"On the other hand, there must be actual present knowledge of the present facts which make an act dangerous.",0,0,0,0,0,0
