"So, if a man does an act with intent to commit a felony, and thereby accidentally kills another; for instance, if he fires at chickens, intending to steal them, and accidentally kills the owner, whom he does not see.",1,0,0,0,0,0
Such a case as this last seems hardly to be reconcilable with the general principles which have been laid down.,0,0,0,0,0,0
