"There is another class of cases in which intent plays an important part, for quite different reasons from those which have been offered to account for the law of malicious mischief.",0,0,0,0,0,0
The most obvious examples of this class are criminal attempts.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"Attempt and intent, of course, are two distinct things.",0,0,0,0,0,0
Intent to commit a crime is not itself criminal.,1,0,0,0,0,0
There is no law against a man's intending to commit a murder the day after tomorrow.,0,0,0,0,0,0
The law only deals with conduct.,0,0,0,0,0,0
