/3/ It was trespass quare clausum.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"The defendant pleaded that he owned adjoining land, upon which was a thorn hedge; that he cut the thorns, and that they, against his will (ipso invito), fell on the plaintiff's land, and the defendant went quickly upon the same, and took them, which was the trespass complained of.",1,0,0,0,0,0
