"The answer must be, by experience.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"But there is one point which has been left ambiguous in the preceding Lecture and here, and which must be touched upon.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"It has been assumed that conduct which [148] the man of ordinary intelligence would perceive to be dangerous under the circumstances, would be blameworthy if pursued by him.",1,1,1,1,1,1
"It might not be so, however.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"Suppose that, acting under the threats of twelve armed men, which put him in fear of his life, a man enters another's close and takes a horse.",1,1,0,1,1,0
