"He who snaps a cap upon a gun pointed in the direction of another person, known by him to be present, is answerable for the consequences.",1,1,1,1,1,1
"The question what a prudent man would do under given circumstances is then equivalent to the question what are the teachings of experience as to the dangerous character of this or that conduct under these or those circumstances; and as the teachings of experience are matters of fact, it is easy to see why the jury should be consulted with regard to them.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"They are, however, facts of a special and peculiar function.",0,0,0,0,0,0
