"/3/ In former days, at least, they might inquire about it in pais after a demurrer.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"/4/ They may act on the statement of a special jury, as in the time of Lord Mansfield and his successors, or upon the finding of a common jury based on the testimony of witnesses, as is the practice to-day in this country.",1,1,1,1,1,1
"But many instances will be found the text-books which show that, when the facts are ascertained, they soon cease to be referred to, and give place to a rule of law.",1,0,0,0,0,0
