"/1/ He set up in defence that enemies of the king broke into the prison and carried off the prisoner, against the will of the defendant.",0,0,0,0,0,0
The question was whether this was a good defence.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"The court said that, if alien enemies of the king, for instance the French, released the prisoner, or perhaps if the burning of the prison gave him a chance to escape, the excuse would be good, because then [the defendant] has remedy against no one.",1,1,1,1,1,1
