"Thus far, nothing has been said with regard to the custody of servants.",0,0,0,0,0,0
"It is a well-known doctrine of the criminal law, that a servant who criminally converts property of his master intrusted to him and in his custody as servant, is guilty of theft, because he is deemed to have taken the property from his master's possession.",1,0,0,0,0,0
"This is equivalent to saying that a servant, having the custody of his master's property as servant, has not possession of that property, and it is so stated in the Year Books.",1,0,0,0,0,0
