"We may now pass from undertakings that certain facts are true at the time of making the contract, to undertakings that certain facts shall be true at some later time,--that is, to promises properly so called.",0,0,0,0,0,0
The question is when performance of the promise on one side is a condition to the obligation of the contract on the other.,0,0,0,0,0,0
