/1/ A right could be attached to a manor by prescription to have a convent sing in the manor chapel.,0,0,0,0,0,0
/2/ A right might be gained by like means to have certain land fenced by the owner of the neighboring lot.,0,0,0,0,0,0
"/3/ Now, it may readily be conceded that even rights like the last two, when attached to land, were looked at as property, and were spoken of as the subject of grant.",0,0,0,0,0,0
